******
[2] Malaysia
Date: Wed 3 Mar 2010
Source: Taiwan News, Associated Press [edited]
<http://www.etaiwannews.com/etn/news_content.php?id=1195853&lang=eng>


An official says Malaysia is urging people to take precautions
against dengue fever after a rise in deaths from the mosquito-borne
virus. Health Ministry official Lim Chau Leng says 31 people have
died after catching the disease in the 1st 2 months of the year
[2010], compared with 28 deaths in the same period last year [2009].
More than 8000 people caught dengue fever in January and February
[2010], the peak time for infection after monsoon rains. Last week
alone, 6 people died.

Lim said Friday [26 Feb 2010] that people must keep their
surroundings clean and destroy mosquito breeding grounds, such as
stagnant pools of water. They should seek treatment if they have such
symptoms as high fever, joint pains and nausea.

