[3] Australia (North Queensland)
Date: Fri 5 Mat 2010
Source: ABC (Australian Broadcasting Co.) [edited]
<http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2010/03/05/2837748.htm>


Queensland Health says it has been 3 months since the last case was
diagnosed. Health authorities in north Queensland have declared the
dengue fever outbreak in Townsville over. There were 13 cases of
locally-acquired dengue between November and December last year
[2009].

Queensland Health says it has been 3 months since the last case was diagnosed.

[Byline: Penny Timms]

--
