[4] Brazil (Sao Paulo)
Date: Wed 3 Mar 2010
Source: O Globo [in Portuguese, trans, Mod.TY, edited]
<http://oglobo.globo.com/cidades/sp/mat/2010/03/03/hospital-da-baixada-santista-vive-cenario-de-epidemia-com-39-dos-internados-com-febre-hemorragica-da-dengue-915979675.asp>


The scenario recorded in units of the Hospital Ana Costa in Santos,
in Santos Baixada [an area that includes Bertioga, Cubatao, Guaruja,
Itanhaem, Mongagua, Peruibe, Praia Grande, Santos and Sao Vicente] on
the Sao Paulo coast, is an epidemic of dengue, a situation soon to be
officially confirmed in the region. Among the 59 admissions of
patients over 12 years of age, 22 had a diagnosis of DHF. Among
children, 12 of 28 [hospital] admissions had this [clinical] picture.
Thus, 39 percent of cases hospitalized in the Hospital Ana Costa
Hospital up to 1 Mar [2010] were DHF.

The study also shows that 173 suspected cases of dengue were reported
in the days between 11 Jan-11 Mar [2010] just in the Santos unit. The
data were presented this morning [3 Mar 2010] by the hospital's
director, Jose Luiz Boechat Paione, the infectious disease physician
and Technical Director of the Division of Communicable Infectious and
Parasitic diseases of FMUSP [Faculty of Medicine, University of Sao
Paulo], Evaldo Stanislau Affonso de Araujo, and the person
responsible for the department of pediatrics, Ana Costa, Paulo Sergio
Ciola.

With data and professional experience, Palone and Araujo believe the
hospital presents a scenario of an epidemic. They cannot say that
situation is the same throughout the state but believe it is an
expected picture that very soon will be officially confirmed.

The Santos Baixada recorded 763 confirmed cases, according to the
last official total reported. Santos and Guaruja already confirmed 3
deaths from the disease.

